exploring the simulation result waveform:

[1] launch GTKWave. 
[2] open TopBench.vcd using "Open New Tab" item under "File" menu. 
[3] three panes in the window: SST, Signals, Waves. 
    choose from SST to add to Signals: 
        TopBench.top.clock
        TopBench.top.reset
        TopBench.uart.uart_txd
        TopBench.uart.tx_bitcount[3:0]
        TopBench.uart.tx_count16[3:0]
        TopBench.uart.tx_busy
        TopBench.uart.txdata[31:0]
        TopBench.uart.write_en
    zoom out to show the full 120us time range. 
    zoom in and move left and right to explore details of signals.

a few things can be seen: 

[1] reset is asserted twice: once at time 0, another at 60us. it simulated twice the waveforms from reset. 
[2] uart bitcount is running, but never finished a word in 60us period of whole simulated time. 
[3] uart tx_data is 3A which is the ASCII value of character ':'. that is the 2nd character sent to uart. 
    the tx_data of first character '0' is 0x30 which needs to be zoomed in to see at the start of first word. 


